         <abstract>
            <p>Using a large sample of credit unions, this paper compares the Altman and the Meyer and Pifer methods of bankruptcy prediction. The simpler Altman model performs just as well as or better than the more theoretically appealing Meyer and Pifer model, whose additional sophistication does not appear to be justified by any increase in predictive ability.</p>
         </abstract>
